                <note rend="inline" type="source">611.1731/15: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Minister in Nicaragua</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Ramer</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1924-01-15T19:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">January 15, 1924—7 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>3. Your despatch 281, September 22, 1923. Consul at Corinto telegraphs, January
                    11, that customs authorities inform him that American products are not accorded
                    the reductions of the French treaty. Department had understood reductions
                    accorded to United States under decree of August 23, 1911. Report briefly by
                    telegraph and fully by mail.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hughes</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
